<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 11:08AM CST  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Sequatchie,
south central Bledsoe, northeastern Marion and central Hamilton
Counties through 1245 PM EST/1145 AM CST/...
At 1208 PM EST/1108 AM CST/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm over Whitwell, or 11 miles southwest of Dunlap, moving
east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Dunlap, Soddy-Daisy, Signal Mountain, Walden, Lakesite,
Whitwell, Fairmount, Powells Crossroads and Martin Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
